This paper is about medical image segmentation using deep learning and generative adversarial networks. The primary focus is on retinal vessel segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also mention the use of encoder-decoder style network architecture, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) applications such as image and video processing. Finally, the paper discusses the use of structured prediction, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
